<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Three Ring Wins Davona Dale Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HALLANDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Three Ring, who never has finished out  
of the money, ran away with the Grade 2 $100,000 Davona Dale Stakes 
for 3-year-old fillies at Gulfstream Park Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	In front from the start, the 4-to-5 favorite turned it on at the  
top of the stretch and won by 14 3/4 lengths. 
</P>
<P>
	Golden Temper was second and Gold From The West finished third  
in a field of five going a mile and 70 yards. 
</P>
<P>
	The Florida-bred daughter of Notebook, ridden by John R.  
Velazquez, was timed in 1:41 2/5 and paid $3.60, $2.80 and $2.10. 
Golden Temper paid $4.40 and $2.10. Gold From The West paid $2.10 
to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Three Ring broke on top and was in control throughout. She led  
Golden Temper by two lengths turning down the backstretch, with 
Gold From The West next. The order of the first three did not 
change the rest of the way -- but the margin surely did. 
</P>
<P>
	Turning for home, Three Ring opened her lead to three lengths  
and increased it with every single stride. Golden Temper finished 
second by three-quarters of a length over Gold From The West. 
</P>
<P>
	Owned by Barry Schwartz, Three Ring has won four of seven  
starts, with two seconds and one third, earning $533,440. Last 
year, she won the $125,000 Susan's Girl and the $408,000 My Dear 
Girl divisions of the Florida Stallion Stakes at Calder Race 
Course. 
</P>
<P>
	Trainer Eddie Plesa Jr. tried blinkers on Three Ring Sunday for  
the first time, and it obviously made a difference. 
</P>
<P>
	``I worked her with blinkers a couple of weeks ago, and I could  
tell right away she was much better with them on,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Velazquez, who rode two earlier winners Sunday, has ridden Three  
Ring in all but her first start. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
